stanford.androidlib

Class SimpleDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • stanford.androidlib.SimpleDialog

  • public final class SimpleDialog
extends Object
    A utility class for showing various kinds of dialog boxes. 
     SimpleDialog.with(this).showAlertDialog("Hello!");

      • showProgressDialog

        public SimpleProgressDialog showProgressDialog(String message)

      • showProgressDialog

        public SimpleProgressDialog showProgressDialog(String message,
                                               int max)
        Shows a progress dialog with a progress bar. The given max is the highest value the progress bar can reach; once it reaches that point, the client should presumably tell the progress dialog to dismiss() itself. Pass a max <= 0 for an indeterminate dialog that does not have a specific maximum.
